471
00:35:36,120 --> 00:35:39,480
See, we did it as a joke to cheer
you up. We didn't think
we'd be the actual buyers.

472
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:44,199
Then he said you said you thought
it was the alien, and we thought...

473
00:35:44,199 --> 00:35:46,440
well, that's funny, innit?

474
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:48,799
Come on, Eugene, get real.

475
00:35:48,799 --> 00:35:51,599
But then we thought,
"Let him dream, man.

476
00:35:51,599 --> 00:35:55,480
"Life's short and really boring."

477
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:57,800
So then
we went on betting and then...

478
00:35:57,800 --> 00:36:01,600
You bid 15,000 for the eye?

479
00:36:01,600 --> 00:36:03,520
Not us. No. No way.

480
00:36:03,520 --> 00:36:06,000
It turns out there
was real interest.

481
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:09,120
Someone else bid the fifteen
thou, but then HE got greedy.

482
00:36:09,120 --> 00:36:11,640
Ketchup, please. He just couldn't
resist one more measly little bid.

483
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:15,679
£15,005.50. And then, well nothing.

484
00:36:15,679 --> 00:36:17,400
Nada. Endville.

485
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:20,200
OK, shut the fuck up, Gary.

486
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:23,919
Point is, we bought it.

487
00:36:23,919 --> 00:36:26,040
We are the purchasers.

488
00:36:26,040 --> 00:36:28,680
Ta-dah!

489
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:32,840
So you've got
£15,005.50 on you, have you?

490
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:34,999
We've got £34.

491
00:36:34,999 --> 00:36:39,439
£34, Eugene. That's not a
poke in the eye, so to speak.

492
00:36:39,439 --> 00:36:41,519
I'm calling a cab.

493
00:36:41,519 --> 00:36:43,279
Hey slow down.

494
00:36:46,999 --> 00:36:49,640
Banana milkshake?
Thank you.

495
00:36:51,840 --> 00:36:55,159
If it's all such a sodding
joke, why do you even want it?

496
00:36:55,159 --> 00:36:57,679
I got a friend
with a visual impairment.

497
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:01,479
You're going to re-sell
it online, aren't you?

498
00:37:01,479 --> 00:37:08,040
You cheap little gits. You know
he's out there... Who? The alien,
and he'll pay anything.

499
00:37:08,040 --> 00:37:12,480
Eugene, man, I'm as partial as the
next guy to a bit of sci-fi but...

500
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:14,639
A green geezer with six eyes?

501
00:37:14,639 --> 00:37:17,880
Get real, guy.
I checked the bid history.

502
00:37:17,880 --> 00:37:23,359
Mr C Blackstaff is a collector of
alien ephemera and Nazi memorabilia.

503
00:37:23,359 --> 00:37:25,479
Also beanie babies.

504
00:37:25,479 --> 00:37:29,080
Teeny bit cuckoo,
but endearingly rich.

505
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:33,120
And if he's willing to pay 15,000...

506
00:37:37,879 --> 00:37:39,079
Oi!

507
00:37:39,079 --> 00:37:41,880
So now they're
inconveniencing customers.

508
00:37:41,880 --> 00:37:44,040
You stepped in? Well, I tried.

509
00:37:47,040 --> 00:37:49,959
I didn't really know what
the eye was any more...

510
00:37:52,879 --> 00:37:56,880
..but I was damned if I was
going to let it go for £34
and a banana milkshake.

511
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:07,960
Heimlich!

512
00:38:07,960 --> 00:38:11,160
Heimlich! What are you doing?
Getting the goods, idiot!
Get the milkshake!

513
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:17,679
Well, that's just not
acceptable behaviour.

514
00:38:17,679 --> 00:38:22,760
Not at a Happy Cook. They were making
a public spectacle of themselves.

515
00:38:28,800 --> 00:38:31,360
And that was it,
he was out the door and gone.

516
00:38:31,360 --> 00:38:33,799
Oh, my God! That is so weird!

517
00:38:33,799 --> 00:38:35,839
You bastards! You are so dead!

518
00:38:35,839 --> 00:38:39,040
I mean, Josh, you're just a
dickhead, but Gary...

519
00:38:39,040 --> 00:38:41,200
We were... I mean, we were mates.
Hi, doll.

520
00:38:41,200 --> 00:38:43,200
Are you talking to me? Yeah.

521
00:38:43,200 --> 00:38:48,000
Sorry. Look, I don't know whether
you remember us from last week. Yes.

522
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:51,679
Yeah, now the thing is, there may be
people coming in to ask questions.

523
00:38:51,679 --> 00:38:54,040
A woman specifically. And I think...

524
00:38:54,040 --> 00:38:57,600
Josh. ..it would be in your best
interests if... Shut up, Josh.

525
00:38:57,600 --> 00:38:59,359
The woman is complying, man.

526
00:39:02,719 --> 00:39:05,760
OK. Cool.

527
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:11,119
What did you do that for, twat?

528
00:39:11,119 --> 00:39:12,439
I miss him!

529
00:39:22,039 --> 00:39:24,400
So he ran out the door and
you two ran after him? Yeah.

530
00:39:24,400 --> 00:39:25,920
We chased him across the car park.

531
00:39:25,920 --> 00:39:27,599
But Eugene was quite fast.

532
00:39:27,599 --> 00:39:29,560
Josh had new shoes,
he was making a fuss...

533
00:39:29,560 --> 00:39:31,360
Hey, hey... You are overweight.

534
00:39:31,360 --> 00:39:33,919
He hared across the road
and we lost him.

535
00:39:33,919 --> 00:39:36,760
Honest to God.

536
00:39:36,760 --> 00:39:38,439
OK.

537
00:39:38,439 --> 00:39:41,000
That's it.

538
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:43,000
OK.

539
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:47,400
All those cars. All those
lives moving through space...

540
00:39:47,400 --> 00:39:53,560
Hello.
Can you give me the number for Filey
Garage, Filey Road, Cardiff, please?

541
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:59,119
All that humanity whizzing by in a
frenzy of burgers and chips,

542
00:39:59,119 --> 00:40:03,119
bank holiday fun, burst
tyres, screaming kids

543
00:40:03,119 --> 00:40:05,800
and sudden heart-attacks.
Put me through, thanks.

544
00:40:09,120 --> 00:40:10,959
Mr Jones?

545
00:40:10,959 --> 00:40:16,320
You don't know me,
but I'm a friend of your son Eugene.

546
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:20,840
I've got some bad news, I'm afraid.
Now I remember.

547
00:40:20,840 --> 00:40:24,999
Apart from a buzzing in my ear
where Josh whacked me, I felt good.

548
00:40:24,999 --> 00:40:27,760
I was running across a
field on a Saturday morning.

549
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:30,040
The smell of exhaust
and banana milkshake,

550
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:36,720
a slight nausea, heart beating too
fast cos I wasn't that fit - all the
stuff that tells you you're alive.

551
00:40:45,800 --> 00:40:49,640
By rights, I should
be well pissed off -

552
00:40:49,640 --> 00:40:51,720
my mates had cheated on me

553
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:55,840
and I didn't meet any aliens, but
I realised that when I swallowed the

554
00:40:55,840 --> 00:41:03,360
eye at the Happy Cook, I was given
a chance to look back on my life
and see it for what it really was.

555
00:41:03,360 --> 00:41:07,240
Gary, I'm going to miss you.

556
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:13,920
Not the biggest turn-out you
could hope for, but still.

557
00:41:13,920 --> 00:41:15,679
I wish I could...

558
00:41:15,679 --> 00:41:19,360
God, Gwen, I wish I could say
thank you.

559
00:41:20,920 --> 00:41:22,999
And here he is...

560
00:41:24,960 --> 00:41:26,680
..my dad,

561
00:41:26,680 --> 00:41:29,640
only 14 years late.

562
00:41:40,359 --> 00:41:43,880
So, now I know it wasn't
my fault my dad left,

563
00:41:43,880 --> 00:41:47,279
and that, of course,
he wasn't Superman

564
00:41:47,279 --> 00:41:49,839
or an alien,

565
00:41:49,839 --> 00:41:52,600
he's just an ordinary bloke.

566
00:41:54,919 --> 00:41:56,399
Eugene...

567
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:02,120
He was a good boy,

568
00:42:02,120 --> 00:42:04,920
but somehow...

569
00:42:04,920 --> 00:42:07,999
things went wrong. I wasn't there.

570
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:12,799
I wish I could have
seen him...before...

571
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:20,119
An ordinary bloke
who made a mess of things.

572
00:42:21,960 --> 00:42:24,079
# Oh, Danny Boy

573
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:30,040
# The pipes, the pipes are calling

574
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:36,999
# From glen to glen
and down the mountainside

575
00:42:36,999 --> 00:42:43,840
# The summer's gone
and all the flowers dying

576
00:42:43,840 --> 00:42:51,160
# Tis you must go
and I must stay behind

577
00:42:51,160 --> 00:42:54,679
# But come ye back

578
00:42:54,679 --> 00:42:59,520
# When summer's in the meadow

579
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:03,200
# Or when the valley's

580
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:07,719
# Hushed and white with snow

581
00:43:07,719 --> 00:43:11,079
# And I'll be there

582
00:43:11,079 --> 00:43:13,199
# In sunshine

583
00:43:13,199 --> 00:43:16,359
# And in shadow... #

584
00:43:18,720 --> 00:43:19,880
No!

585
00:43:21,199 --> 00:43:23,640
Not yet.

586
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:27,520
Dad made a mess of things
and went away,

587
00:43:27,520 --> 00:43:31,719
and that's a shame really,
it's a terrible pity,

588
00:43:31,719 --> 00:43:33,800
because we missed each other.

589
00:43:35,400 --> 00:43:37,039
Completely.

590
00:43:50,760 --> 00:43:52,520
You know, 28 is one of
those perfect numbers.

591
00:43:52,520 --> 00:43:54,759
It's equal to the
sum of its divisors.

592
00:43:56,320 --> 00:43:58,479
I'm 28.

593
00:43:58,479 --> 00:43:59,959
I was 28.

594
00:44:02,520 --> 00:44:04,559
I think I'm going to
have to go soon, Gwen.

595
00:44:04,559 --> 00:44:07,080
Oh, God.

596
00:44:07,080 --> 00:44:08,559
Yeah.

597
00:44:10,959 --> 00:44:15,799
Also, 28 centimetres per second
is the top speed of a lone lobster.

598
00:44:15,799 --> 00:44:18,319
Oh, hi.

599
00:44:18,319 --> 00:44:21,199
Thank you. I'm sorry I
had to ask you to do that.

600
00:44:21,199 --> 00:44:22,680
Yeah, no problem.

601
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:35,920
So, if it's the eye
that's been keeping me here,

602
00:44:35,920 --> 00:44:39,879
now it's no longer inside me, why
the hell am I still hanging around?

603
00:44:45,199 --> 00:44:46,519
Eugene?

604
00:44:50,120 --> 00:44:53,519
The eye is in the bag now,
rather than in you.

605
00:44:53,519 --> 00:44:55,000
Are you...?

606
00:45:05,920 --> 00:45:08,199
Hello, stranger! Did you get it?
Yeah, I got it.

607
00:45:10,999 --> 00:45:12,760
Impressive.

608
00:45:12,760 --> 00:45:14,959
Well, we haven't done
the tests yet, so...

609
00:45:14,959 --> 00:45:16,759
Come on. We've got to go.

610
00:45:16,759 --> 00:45:20,080
Jack, can you give me five? Yeah.

611
00:45:39,279 --> 00:45:44,440
In an average lifetime, the human
heart will beat two million times.

612
00:45:44,440 --> 00:45:50,599
You'll produce over eight
thousand gallons of saliva
and grow 350 miles of hair.

613
00:45:52,159 --> 00:45:54,920
You'll eat the equivalent
in weight of six elephants.

614
00:45:54,920 --> 00:45:59,800
Oh, isn't life amazing! Gwen!

615
00:45:59,800 --> 00:46:02,359
GWEN!

616
00:46:02,359 --> 00:46:04,639
GWEN!

617
00:46:20,840 --> 00:46:24,439
Hi. Oh, my God.

618
00:46:24,439 --> 00:46:27,119
Eugene! Are you OK?

619
00:46:27,119 --> 00:46:29,799
It is so good to see you.

620
00:46:29,799 --> 00:46:31,960
Eugene, you're on my leg.

621
00:46:31,960 --> 00:46:33,559
Sorry! Sorry. No, no, it's fine.

622
00:46:33,559 --> 00:46:37,080
It's fine. It's fine. It's fine.

623
00:46:39,080 --> 00:46:40,720
Can he see me?

624
00:46:40,720 --> 00:46:43,039
(Eugene...) He can see me!

625
00:46:46,920 --> 00:46:48,919
Thanks.

626
00:46:48,919 --> 00:46:53,160
No, thank you. Thank you.
You just saved my life.

627
00:46:53,160 --> 00:46:54,720
That's OK.

628
00:46:56,359 --> 00:47:00,840
That's unbelievable.
That's un-bloody-believable.

629
00:47:00,840 --> 00:47:03,399
Oh, God...

630
00:47:03,399 --> 00:47:04,839
I think that's it.

631
00:47:13,119 --> 00:47:15,319
Goodbye, Gwen.

632
00:47:20,440 --> 00:47:23,439
Don't go now, Eugene.

633
00:47:23,439 --> 00:47:25,440
Eugene, please don't go now.

634
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:29,039
Eugene, please...

635
00:47:31,279 --> 00:47:32,959
Please!

636
00:47:32,959 --> 00:47:39,080
The average life is full of
near misses and absolute hits,
of great love and small disasters.

637
00:47:39,080 --> 00:47:44,280
It's made up of banana milkshakes,
loft insulation and random shoes.

638
00:47:44,280 --> 00:47:47,040
It's dead ordinary, and
truly, truly amazing.

639
00:47:47,040 --> 00:47:50,080
What you've got to realise is,
it's all here, now.

640
00:47:50,080 --> 00:47:52,440
So breathe deep and swallow it whole.

641
00:47:52,440 --> 00:47:58,360
Because take it from me,
life just whizzes by,
and then, all of a sudden, it's...

642
00:48:00,799 --> 00:48:04,239
At least it wasn't a
spaceship full of aliens.

643
00:48:04,239 --> 00:48:07,239
Which year? I need to know. 1953.

644
00:48:07,239 --> 00:48:11,079
Just three lost people who've
somehow become our responsibility.

645
00:48:11,079 --> 00:48:15,759
A man like you,
out of his time, alone and scared.

646
00:48:15,759 --> 00:48:18,360
I hate this filthy stinking place!

647
00:48:18,360 --> 00:48:21,800
I died once.
It's like two separate worlds.

648
00:48:21,800 --> 00:48:25,440
There's Torchwood...then
there's real life.

649
00:48:27,679 --> 00:48:29,919
I'm scared.

